## N+1 Query Problem

### The Problem

```ruby
# BAD: N+1 query (1 query for articles, N queries for users)
articles = Article.limit(10)
articles.each do |article|
  puts article.user.name  # Separate query for each article!
end

# Generates:
# SELECT * FROM articles LIMIT 10
# SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = 1
# SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = 2
# SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = 3
# ... (10 queries total = 1 + 10)
```

### The Solution: Eager Loading

```ruby
# GOOD: 2 queries total (1 for articles, 1 for users)
articles = Article.includes(:user).limit(10)
articles.each do |article|
  puts article.user.name  # No additional query!
end

# Generates:
# SELECT * FROM articles LIMIT 10
# SELECT * FROM users WHERE id IN (1, 2, 3, ...)
# (2 queries total)
```

